<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2014-04-30</DATELINE><TITLE>Careers in Virology: Public Health Opportunities for Early-Career Basic Scientists</TITLE><BODY>Undergraduate, graduate, and postdoctoral scientists trained as virologists can play critical roles in public health, such as in health science policy, epidemiology, and national defense. Despite a need for basic science backgrounds within these fields, finding entry-level careers can be challenging. Volunteer opportunities are a great way for scientists to experience public health careers while still in school, and this article describes volunteering with the Medical Reserve Corps and outlines unique postgraduate opportunities for early-career virologists.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>